        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 4:38PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM CDT/337 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 8 miles southeast of Whites City, or 23 miles south of
Carlsbad, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whites City and Carlsbad Caverns National Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
